rdf:Description.lla:note: Note on Crew List - Cardiff to Constantinople via various places. 'not to exceed two years'.
Note in ship's log - 'discharged through illness at Queenstown 30th March 1867'
Note in ship's log about spasmodic attendance on board as was suffering from venereal disease. Had to go to the hospital. Dates given in log.
Note on crew list - Deserted Mary Ann at Odessa. Note in ships's log.
Cork to Quebec. Voyage not to exceed twelve months.
Ship's log - Harry Frost but no mention of this man
